(646, 3624, '_madxartwork_data', '[{\"id\":\"529181fe\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"55029bc2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2ff0515b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>We are here to minimise cost, time and risk to you to ensure high quality product reaches its final destination<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"},{\"id\":\"a64c109\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/indogoods.id\\/media\\/2020\\/03\\/product-inspection.jpg\",\"id\":3596}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f3e918a\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"59246db\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5d3ea69\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Quality expectations and the range of safety requirements that you must achieve become more complex. QC has the right systems, processes and procedures to help you meet the requirements and to deliver quality products in a timely manner.<br \\/>Quality Control Inspections Procedure<br \\/>Typical quality control inspections include four primary steps. Depending on the product, your experience with the supplier, and other factors, any one, or all of these, may apply to your needs. With the right systems, processes and procedures of quality control inspections, we can monitor product quality to reduce risk, improve efficiency and ensure compliance with contractual or regulatory requirements, build a stronger and more resilient business with the potential to grow and surpass your competition<\\/p><p>Pre-production Inspections<br \\/>Prior to production, our quality control inspection of raw materials and components will confirm whether these meet your specifications and are available in quantities sufficient to meet the production schedule. An inspection of machinery and materials will be made before the production.and Ensure the factory\\u2019s machinery can meet your quality needs while guaranteeing the actual materials to be used in production are the materials agreed to<\\/p><p>During Production Inspections<br \\/>During production, the products are inspected to verify that quality requirements and specifications are being met. This process is useful in cases of repeated defects in production. It can help identify where in the process the problem occurs and provide objective input for solutions to resolve the production issues. We ensure production processes and capacity \\u2013 enabling you greater control and sufficient time to improve production quality. When at least 20% of production is completed, our qualified inspector is sent to your factory to inspect production quality and status. Follow our checklist or your custom inspection requirements.<\\/p><p>Pre Shipment Inspections (PSI)<br \\/>An on-site product inspection ensures the conformity of production to your specifications prior to shipment.<br \\/>When at least 80% of production is completed and packaged, our qualified inspector is sent to your factory to inspect the finished production following our checklist or your custom requirements, protecting you from shipping non-conforming product. After production is completed, a pre shipment inspection can be done to verify that the goods being shipped have been manufactured according to your requirements.<\\/p><p>Container Loading Inspections<br \\/>Container Loading Inspection . We check that your order is complete and securely loaded into the container before shipment. This is the final opportunity to confirm compliance with your requirements in terms of quantity, assortment, and packaging and Ensure the product you pay for is the product that ships. Prior to making final payment arrangements, guarantee you finished and packaged goods meet your specifications (product type and quantity) and are securely loaded for shipment.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"89e2d6c\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"e030041\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"254c215\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Benefits of Quality Control Inspections :<br \\/>\\u2022 Customers expect to buy qualified, health and safety products<br \\/>\\u2022 Ensure every procedure goes well at every production stage<br \\/>\\u2022 Verify quality at the source and don\\u2019t pay for defective goods<br \\/>\\u2022 Avoid recalls and reputation damage<br \\/>\\u2022 Anticipate production and shipment delays<br \\/>\\u2022 Minimize your quality control budget<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
