(724, 3634, '_madxartwork_data', '[{\"id\":\"4f97784a\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2bf8bed\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3da42e1e\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"Check the status of your shipment with regular updates\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"8ce16d1\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b68a993\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"eb5d9a4\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/indogoods.id\\/media\\/2020\\/03\\/shipping-check.jpg\",\"id\":3598}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"bda74bb\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3d97ba6\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d9bf919\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>A lot of supply chain disputes, around the world, arise due to damages to the products during the loading phase. As such, it is important for businesses to get a thorough container loading inspection carried out before dispatching products to the customers<br \\/>Container loading check is carried out during the loading of containers with your shipment. The inspection ensures that the loading of your shipment is carried out in accordance with the internationally accepted rules and regulations.<br \\/>The container inspection is carried out right after the pre-shipment inspection and it ensures that your products are packed correctly and will not get damaged during the shipment process.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"32f0770\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"40bb6c6\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"slider_delay\":\"5000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"46bc5d7\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>There is nothing more disappointing for the client to receive broken or damaged products and that too because of the loading company\\u2019s faults. As such, container loading inspection has multiple benefits for your business that you must not overlook. Here are a few ways that you will benefit from a professional container loading audit:<\\/p><ul><li>It greatly helps to avoid any broken\\/damaged products during transport.<\\/li><li>Inspection also ensures that the products are properly handled and are not damaged during the loading process.<\\/li><li>Container loading inspection greatly saves time and money by reducing the number of damaged items.<\\/li><li>Your customers feel very satisfied with on-time and undamaged delivery.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
